results.name: If p is the product of k1-th prime, k2-th prime,..,kr-th prime then set a(n)=n-k1*k2*..*kr, if p is the k-th prime then set=n-k, a(1)=1 by convention.
results.author: _Juri-Stepan Gerasimov_, Jun 03 2010
